The paper discusses the minimum number of NOT operators in a Boolean formula representing a Boolean function, which is related to circuit complexity theory. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves logical reasoning and Boolean algebra, which are related to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the paper uses arguments based on the study of circuit complexity, which is related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper involves information theory, which is related to cs.IT (Information Theory).
